Perfect! Now I have enough information to create a comprehensive plan. Let me write the exploration report:

# Comprehensive Chat Template Infrastructure Analysis for llama.cpp

## Executive Summary

I've thoroughly explored the llama.cpp codebase to understand the chat template infrastructure. The system uses a **two-tiered template handling approach**: a fallback automatic parser for generic templates, plus specialized handlers for models with complex/unique formatting requirements. For "mistral-instruct-v3", you'll need to create a specialized handler (similar to Ministral 3) rather than relying on auto-parsing.

---

## 1. Main Implementation Files

### Core Files:
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/common/chat.h`** - Header with all data structures and public API
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/common/chat.cpp`** - Main implementation (~1800+ lines)
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/common/chat-auto-parser.h`** - Auto-parser struct definitions
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/common/chat-auto-parser-helpers.h`** - Helper functions for auto-parsing

### Supporting Files:
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/common/chat-peg-parser.h/.cpp`** - PEG parser for output parsing
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/common/chat-auto-parser-generator.cpp`** - Auto-generates PEG parsers from templates
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/common/chat-diff-analyzer.cpp`** - Analyzes template differences

### Test Files:
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/tests/test-chat-template.cpp`** - Template testing framework
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/tests/test-chat.cpp`** - Integration tests for specific templates
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/tests/test-chat-auto-parser.cpp`** - Auto-parser tests
- **`/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/tests/test-chat-peg-parser.cpp`** - PEG parser tests

---

## 2. Existing Template Handler Structure

### Handler Pattern Overview

All specialized template handlers follow this consistent pattern:

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_[MODEL_NAME](
    const common_chat_template &            tmpl,
    const autoparser::generation_params &   inputs) {

    common_chat_params data;

    // 1. Prepare adjusted messages if needed
    auto adjusted_messages = json::array();
    // ... message transformation logic ...

    // 2. Apply template with adjusted messages
    data.prompt = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs, adjusted_messages);

    // 3. Set output format
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;

    // 4. Define preserved tokens (prevent tokenization)
    data.preserved_tokens = {
        "[TOKEN1]",
        "[TOKEN2]",
        // ...
    };

    // 5. Build custom PEG parser using peg_builder
    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        // Customize parsing rules
        return p.prefix(generation_prompt) + (reasoning << p.content(p.rest()));
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();

    // 6. Optional: Build grammar for tool calls
    if (include_grammar) {
        data.grammar_lazy = ...;
        data.grammar = build_grammar([&](const common_grammar_builder & builder) {
            // Build tool calling grammar
            parser.build_grammar(builder, data.grammar_lazy);
        });
        data.grammar_triggers = {
            { COMMON_GRAMMAR_TRIGGER_TYPE_WORD, "[TOOL_CALLS]" }
        };
    }

    // 7. Optional: Support thinking/reasoning
    data.supports_thinking = true;
    data.thinking_start_tag = "[THINK]";
    data.thinking_end_tag = "[/THINK]";

    return data;
}
```

### Existing Specialized Handlers (Located in common/chat.cpp):

1. **`common_chat_params_init_ministral_3`** (Line ~825)
   - Handles Ministral-3 and Mistral Large 3
   - Converts `reasoning_content` to thinking blocks
   - Supports tool calls with `[TOOL_CALLS]`, `[ARGS]` tokens
   - Preserves: `[THINK]`, `[/THINK]`, `[TOOL_CALLS]`, `[ARGS]`

2. **`common_chat_params_init_gpt_oss`** (Line ~942)
   - Handles GPT-OSS models (channel-based structure)
   - Maps `reasoning_content` to `thinking` field
   - Replaces `<|return|>` with `<|end|>` in certain conditions

3. **`common_chat_params_init_functionary_v3_2`** (Line ~1081)
   - Handles recipient-based format: `>>>recipient\n{content}`
   - Preserves: `>>>all`
   - Uses pattern-based grammar trigger: `>>>(?!all)`

4. **`common_chat_params_init_kimi_k2`** (Line ~1175)
   - Handles Kimi K2 thinking models
   - Unique tool call ID format: `functions.<name>:<index>`
   - Supports complex reasoning within tool calls
   - Preserves multiple token markers

5. **`common_chat_params_init_lfm2`** (Line ~1298)
   - Handles LFM2 format
   - Uses `<|tool_list_start|>`, `<|tool_list_end|>` markers

6. **`common_chat_params_init_lfm2_5`** (Line ~1377)
   - Handles LFM2.5 format
   - Uses plain "List of tools: [...]" syntax (no special tokens)

7. **`common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`** (Line ~1446)
   - Handles GigaChat V3
   - Uses `<|role_sep|>` and `<|message_sep|>` markers

---

## 3. Auto-Detection and Registration Mechanism

### Critical Detection Function: `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`

**Location:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775489310550-n1swqf/common/chat.cpp` (Line ~1634)

This function is the **dispatcher** that determines which handler to use:

```cpp
std::optional<common_chat_params> common_chat_try_specialized_template(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const std::string &                   src,
        const autoparser::generation_params & params)
```

